btpd: btpd (BitTorrent client daemon)
btpd:
btpd: BTPD is a bittorrent client consisting of a daemon and client commands
btpd: which can be used to read and/or manipulate the daemon state. 
btpd: The daemon is capable of running several torrents simultaneously 
btpd: and only uses one tcp port. It's fairly low on resource usage 
btpd: and should be perfect for file distribution sites. 
btpd: Efficient downloads and ease of use makes this client a good choice 
btpd: for the casual user as well.
btpd: 
btpd: Homepage: http://www.murmeldjur.se/btpd/
btpd: 

